Always follow clean architecture
Always use Dapper (never EF)
Always update /sql/main.sql when schema changes
Always update /json files when DTO changes
Always keep README.md files up to date (root, /api, /sql, /json)
Always keep modules extensible
Controllers must always reside in Ayora.Api/Controllers
Never place business logic in controllers
Always use services and repositories
Always use async methods
Always use DTOs for API boundaries
Always follow consistent folder conventions:
- Api: Controllers/, Middleware/, Swagger/ (and feature folders must not contain controllers)
- Application: DTOs/, Interfaces/, Services/, Options/
- Infrastructure: Repositories/, Data/, Security/
- Domain: Entities (or Models)/, Interfaces/, Enums/
Always keep folder structure aligned with these conventions (move files + update namespaces/usings when needed)
